author: @MultiSUPERLATIVO
content:
The word "free" can have many interpretations, but at the end of the day, someone paid for that "free." As the ancients said: “there is no such thing as a free lunch”.
Rio's tax payers paid for the concert, as the city's mayor paid out by using taxpayers' money. We all pay a fortune in money for the huge police force apparatus. City surveillance services were mobilized with cars and police personnel (all this is money). The large bank Itaú used money from its clients to pay for the singer's massive amount of cash: Madonna didn't work for free!
